workers’ and peasants’ struggle in the Russian revolution. For that very reason,
the [Leninist] oligarchs exterminated the Kronstadters, some right after the
military victory, the remainder in the dungeons and blockhouses inherited from
the tsarist and bourgeois regime. Understood thus, the date of March 7 [1921]
has to appear as a profoundly painful anniversary for the workers of all
countries. So it is not just among Russian toilers only that the painful memory
of the Kronstadt revolutionaries who perished in the fighting and the survivors
who were left to rot in Bolshevik jails should be reawakened on that date. But
this matter will not be resolved with moaning: aside from the commemoration of
